1
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:36,760
The pulp for the cultural products,

2
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,640
of course we source it locally.

3
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,760
That way, the cost is definitely the lowest.

4
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:41,960
Take a look.

5
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:44,680
It's all clearly shown on this report.

6
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:47,680
Taohua Town has over 30 manufacturers

7
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,200
supplying us with Xuan paper.

8
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,040
And then there are some

9
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,280
who used to produce handmade paper

10
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,360
and have now shifted to producing pulp.

11
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:58,320
Didn't the Xuan family try to shift too,

12
00:01:58,480 --> 00:01:59,000
and fail?

13
00:01:59,160 --> 00:01:59,560
No, no, no.

14
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,680
Hold on a second.

15
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:03,240
Do we really need over 30 suppliers?

16
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:05,520
The big factories think the profits are too low,

17
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:06,480
so they won't do it.

18
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,720
There are many workshop-scale businesses,

19
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:10,560
but their output is very small.

20
00:02:11,039 --> 00:02:12,680
Our Taohua Town Company

21
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,120
is practically becoming a charity.

22
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,560
Handing out relief to them every day.

23
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:17,960
You can't really put it that way.

24
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,160
We source materials locally.

25
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:22,040
If the pulp came from outside,

26
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,680
the cost would definitely be higher.

27
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:25,720
If they weren't making money,

28
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:28,800
would they have stopped making handmade paper

29
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,560
and switched to pulp?

30
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:32,080
If they're making money,

31
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:33,840
that would push up our costs.

32
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,640
So what is that if not handing out relief?

33
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:36,360
Well...

34
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,640
By your logic,

35
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,520
we shouldn't use pulp to mold Xuanbao anymore,

36
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,720
we should use mud instead?

37
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:43,680
Ms. Xin, we were just discussing this.

38
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,800
Didn't expect you.

39
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,720
Why are you discussing this?

40
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,280
Here's the thing.

41
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,120
The Chairman

42
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,560
called me this morning.

43
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:53,080
He told me to hurry up

44
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:56,080
and get the exact data

45
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,280
on our Taohua Town Company's

46
00:02:57,280 --> 00:03:00,520
pulp usage and purchase prices.

47
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,520
So I got anxious

48
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:03,640
and rushed over to look into it.

49
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:05,960
I didn't have time to report to you.

50
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,200
Didn't have time to report to me?

51
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:10,280
But you had time to report to Manager Huang?

52
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,120
My bad, my bad.

53
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:14,240
I wasn't thoughtful enough about this.

54
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,200
Ms. Xin, Mr. Zhang,

55
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,280
you two talk, I'll get back to work.

56
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,160
Huang...

57
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:22,320
Vice President Zhang,

58
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,320
we're all on the same side here,

59
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:26,720
so let's be frank.

60
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,680
Yes, yes, yes.

61
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:32,720
Why is the Chairman asking about pulp data?

62
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:33,880
What does he want to do?

63
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:37,440
All I know is that the group

64
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,200
has acquired a pulp mill

65
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:41,920
downstream on the Qingyi River.

66
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,560
Beyond that, I'm not really sure.

67
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:44,920
Already acquired one?

68
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,920
Why not just ask the Chairman directly?

69
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:51,320
Who am I to...

70
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:52,360
Vice President Zhang,

71
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:57,360
watch out, or the eagle you raise may peck your eye.

72
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,200
How could that be?

73
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,680
Take care on your way out.

74
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,120
Chairman,

75
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,800
Let me do the math for you.

76
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,240
Pulp prices are very transparent.

77
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:10,520
The businesses in Taohua Town,

78
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,360
their profit margins are quite thin.

79
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:15,360
Now, if we acquire a pulp mill,

80
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:17,560
the acquisition itself costs a fortune.

81
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,800
Plus operating costs and management costs.

82
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,800
All added up,

83
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,880
it's way more than what we pay now.

84
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,880
It just doesn't add up.

85
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,080
Ms. Xin,

86
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,480
we've already discussed this.

87
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,920
Why are you still asking?

88
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:32,720
The group's top priority right now

89
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:33,880
is going public.

90
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:35,720
I'm buying this pulp mill

91
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:38,360
to pad the listed company's portfolio.

92
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:39,720
The numbers have to look good, of course.

93
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:41,520
Otherwise, I'd be buying a junk asset.

94
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,800
Alright, Chairman.

95
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,640
But if we drive up costs,

96
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:45,920
the final losses,

97
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:47,280
won't they fall on the company?

98
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:50,360
What I want is performance data!

99
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,920
Oh, Ms. Xin,

100
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:53,880
why can't you get it through your head?

101
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:56,880
No matter how high our own costs are,

102
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,200
we have to use our own.

103
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:58,960
Chairman,

104
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:02,080
our company is based in Taohua Town.

105
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:04,720
If we don't use any Taohua Town companies

106
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,920
to provide our supporting services,

107
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,520
wouldn't that hurt

108
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:09,880
local development?

109
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,640
Let me say it again.

110
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:16,520
The group's interests come above all.

111
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,640
Ms. Xin,

112
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:21,040
can you take a broader view here?

113
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,680
At all times, in every way,

114
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:24,800
you must align with the group's interests.

115
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:28,360
Our Taohua Town branch

116
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:30,360
pays taxes in Taohua Town,

117
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:32,120
hires workers in Taohua Town.

118
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:34,400
I've done nothing wrong by Taohua Town.

119
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:35,160
Am I right?

120
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,960
Peng Ruixue should be thanking me.

121
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:38,800
Isn't that right?

122
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:40,640
Fine.

123
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,320
I understand.

124
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:43,560
Good that you understand.

125
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:45,800
Ms. Xin,

126
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,560
there's a lot more you need to understand.

127
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:50,520
Keep in mind

128
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,840
the mission I sent you to Taohua Town for.

129
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,680
Firmly protect the group's interests.

130
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,320
Your top priority right now

131
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,440
is to terminate

132
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:00,320
the pulp partnership with Taohua Town,

133
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:03,880
and align production with the new mill.

134
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,160
Production must not be delayed.

135
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:06,720
Chairman, I...

136
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:20,880
Sister Xin,

137
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,440
Xuan Yan and the others, just days ago,

138
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,240
were still lobbying me,

139
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:31,880
asking to get more production orders

140
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,880
allocated to Taohua Town businesses.

141
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:35,240
Great.

142
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:37,720
Now look at this.

143
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:39,760
Even the pulp deal is off.

144
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:42,000
How am I supposed to face them?

145
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:45,080
Face them however you have to.

146
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,360
This is the group's decision.

147
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,760
It has nothing to do with you.

148
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:48,560
Yuqing,

149
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:51,720
you've been to those small mills with me.

150
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,240
You've seen it yourself.

151
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,800
For Dayazhai,

152
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,520
an insignificant order

153
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,520
is their livelihood for the entire year.

154
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:02,160
They're just small workshops.

155
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,240
You've seen how they're struggling.

156
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,080
Sister Xin,

157
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:09,000
forgive me for saying this,

158
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,000
but you should look out for yourself first.

159
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:22,440
I know.

160
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,360
I have another suggestion.

161
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:28,200
Next time you talk with the Chairman,

162
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,320
no matter what he says,

163
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:31,080
just listen and do as told.

164
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:32,880
Don't voice your own opinions anymore.

165
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:35,240
There's really no need.

166
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,720
Speaking up will only make him resent you more.

167
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:40,560
Go get back to work.

168
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:46,880
And get some rest early too.

169
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:01,960
And that Dayazhai...

170
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,680
they don't treat us like people.

171
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,400
Do they care if we live or die?

172
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:09,160
One word, and they just cancel everything.

173
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,320
We stocked up on so much raw material.

174
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:13,120
Our entire capital's sunk into it.

175
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:14,440
Then why not sign a contract

176
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,760
to protect your own rights?

177
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,680
They won't sign contracts with us.

178
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,440
They said what?

179
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,280
They said supplier contracts

180
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,720
have to be sent back to the Shenzhen HQ for review.

181
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:23,520
Said it's a hassle.

182
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:24,480
Way too much trouble.

183
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,560
Us common folk are easy to deal with.

184
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,760
We understand everything.

185
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,680
But, but they don't understand us!

186
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,360
Exactly.

187
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,280
That's how it is.

188
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:32,480
You two, calm down.

189
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,760
I'm in the same boat.

190
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:36,159
A week ago they called,

191
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,480
asked me for two tons of pulp.

192
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:38,520
Me and my wife,

193
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:40,480
we worked day and night on it.

194
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:42,880
Finally got it all ready, waiting for pickup.

195
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:44,480
Then suddenly they call and cancel.

196
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,520
Tell me, isn't that a total rip-off?

197
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:46,760
Exactly, exactly.

198
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,440
I wonder if they've run into some

199
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:51,000
force majeure situation.

200
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,440
I get it, I really do,

201
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:54,440
but this is just too sudden.

202
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,800
What's there to understand?

203
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,800
Think how much we sank into labor costs.

204
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,920
Fifty or sixty thousand in raw materials!

205
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:03,320
And we still owe suppliers on credit.

206
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,800
Now we're stuck with all this stock.

207
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:08,160
How are we supposed to get by now?

208
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:08,920
Right? Tell me,

209
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:09,440
what are we supposed to do?

210
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:09,840
Dad.

211
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,320
I don't want to go to school anymore.

212
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,240
I'll come home and help you.

213
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,120
Yingzi!

214
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,440
What kind of nonsense is that?

215
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:17,880
No matter how tough things get,

216
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,120
we don't need you to step in.

217
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,680
You just focus on your studies.

218
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:21,680
What?

219
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:22,560
When you grow up,

220
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:24,320
you want to suffer and toil like us?

221
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:26,520
Yingzi, stay out of grown-up business.

222
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:27,200
You hear me?

223
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,400
Just focus on your studies.

224
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:32,800
Director Lin.

225
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,960
Our factory is just too small.

226
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:36,320
That Wannianhong equipment,

227
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,680
we simply can't afford it.

228
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,400
That wallpaper order you brought us last time,

229
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,680
we did produce some of it.

230
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,320
But then those big factories

231
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:45,120
launched their own wallpaper lines.

232
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,680
Once the prices got slashed,

233
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,120
we handmade shops

234
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,800
can't make a dime anymore.

235
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,120
We were counting on

236
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,800
the pulp business to keep us stable.

237
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:53,800
But now look at this mess.

238
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:56,520
Life's gonna be tough from now on.

239
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:58,440
This move,

240
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,400
looks like I made the wrong call.

241
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:02,240
Our family can't compare to the Xuans,

242
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,400
but it's still our ancestral craft.

243
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:06,720
For generations we've lived by scooping paper.

244
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,240
After enduring all these years,

245
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:10,880
we still couldn't hold on.

246
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,800
We just wanted to earn a little money.

247
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:15,480
Instead, we shot ourselves in the foot.

248
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,000
You're telling me.

249
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,120
Everyone, don't get worked up yet.

250
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:20,480
Here's the deal, give me some time.

251
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:22,000
I'll figure something out for you, okay?

252
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:23,120
Director Lin.

253
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:23,960
Okay, okay, okay.

254
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:24,960
Thank you, thank you.

255
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:25,760
That's wonderful.

256
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,200
It's my duty, my duty.

257
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,120
Thanks, thanks, thanks.

258
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:28,360
You've worked so hard.

259
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:29,400
We really appreciate it.

260
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,760
Now we've got some hope.

261
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:31,720
Exactly, exactly.

262
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:35,040
Nobody does business like Dayazhai.

263
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,600
Not giving us orders is one thing,

264
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,240
but they won't even give us pulp work.

265
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:40,480
I don't really care myself,

266
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:41,840
but how are these small shops supposed to survive?

267
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:42,640
Yeah.

268
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:45,040
My workers are practically playing mahjong now.

269
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,640
Dayazhai is a private company.

270
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,000
If they don't want to give it,

271
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,520
what can you all do about it?

272
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:52,400
Dayazhai's made so much money in Taohua Town,

273
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:55,400
yet they look down on us folks here.

274
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:56,880
Who does business like that?

275
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:57,920
Everyone, see this?

276
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,600
They don't take us seriously at all.

277
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,800
Who does that?

278
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,480
You're the Xuan Paper Association chairman,

279
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:04,480
the big brother of us poor guys.

280
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:06,240
You've got to help us put food on the table.

281
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,120
Yeah, that's right.

282
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,720
Otherwise how are we supposed to live?

283
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,120
Gentlemen, gentlemen, gentlemen.

284
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,200
Everyone, don't get anxious.

285
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:14,520
Chairman Xiao will surely find a way.

286
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,280
Come on.

287
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,360
Even Secretary Peng stepping in didn't work.

288
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,560
Don't bother trying either.

289
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,800
They don't take you as chairman seriously at all.

290
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:23,720
Old Ren, watch what you're saying.

291
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:25,520
Let's stick to the issue.

292
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:26,360
Don't make it personal.

293
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:26,640
Right.

294
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:28,200
Don't drag Brother Min into everything.

295
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,200
Quit butting in, you hear me?

296
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,200
Let me tell you,

297
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,640
I'll make my position clear today.

298
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,480
I, Ren Jiye,

299
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:36,240
though I'm not doing great,

300
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:39,920
I'm not so desperate as to beg from Dayazhai.

301
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:42,320
Let's go.

302
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:43,240
Jiye.

303
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:43,960
Old Ren.

304
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:44,240
Jiye.

305
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,000
What's that supposed to mean?

306
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,000
What do you mean, what do I mean?

307
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:46,960
Turning your back on us, huh?

308
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:47,800
That's exactly what I mean.

309
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:48,480
You...

310
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:49,240
Old Xiao.

311
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,000
What kind of people are these?

312
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,200
My relatives' small workshops

313
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,320
were already struggling to get by.

314
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,880
Now that pulp-making is banned,

315
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,920
you're taking away their livelihood,

316
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:00,240
cutting off their means to survive.

317
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,920
Whether it's the government or the association,

318
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:05,120
whether something needs to be done,

319
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,400
you figure it out yourself.

320
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:12,000
Think it over carefully.

321
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:13,000
Let's go, let's go.

322
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,640
Won't lift a finger to help us.

323
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:16,160
Some association president you are.

324
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:16,400
Think it over carefully.

325
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,000
Alright, alright, that's enough.

326
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:19,520
Won't even try to help.

327
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:20,360
Let's just go.

328
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,000
This...

329
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,640
What is with these people?

330
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,200
President Xiao.

331
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:31,760
I think those two

332
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,760
are trying to grab power and win people over.

333
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,600
But don't worry too much.

334
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,720
A few of those families are my relatives.

335
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,560
I can go talk to them.

336
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:39,760
As for helping with anything else,

337
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:42,080
I really can't do much.

338
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:50,400
See these people's true colors now?

339
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:52,520
Brother Min.

340
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:55,000
Last night, Ren Jiye and Fang Guangping

341
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,120
treated a few big county factories to dinner.

342
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:59,520
They said you and Xin Ran are running a husband-and-wife shop,

343
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:01,880
ganging up to play them.

344
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:04,880
Shut it.

345
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,320
Anything you touch is bound to go bad.

346
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:12,080
Our influence is just too limited.

347
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:13,760
I really want to help them,

348
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:15,960
but I honestly don't know how.

349
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:18,320
That family are good people.

350
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:19,800
All so kind-hearted.

351
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,000
I've known Old Song for nearly twenty years.

352
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:23,960
He may be poor, but his spirit isn't.

353
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,320
No matter how tough things got,

354
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,560
he never gave up on this industry.

355
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,600
That's what I admire most about him.

356
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,000
Did you report the survey results

357
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,880
to your superiors?

358
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:38,760
Secretary Peng is really anxious.

359
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,360
She called Zheng Guohui,

360
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:41,760
but the guy wouldn't even pick up.

361
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,000
Zheng Guohui...

362
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,960
Some big corporate chairman.

363
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,240
So petty-minded.

364
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,840
How about you go talk to Ms. Xin?

365
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,720
After all, you own the copyright and patent.

366
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,480
Your words carry more weight than ours.

367
00:13:57,320 --> 00:14:00,080
I've already made arrangements with Xin Ran.

368
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:02,640
Xuan Yan.

369
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:04,320
The cost of the pulp

370
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:06,040
means nothing to Zheng Guohui.

371
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:07,240
No point fussing over it.

372
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,640
Go over and have a proper talk with him.

373
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:11,920
I have no problem dealing with Zheng Guohui.

374
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:13,400
I'm thinking about Xin Ran.

375
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:15,880
This could easily

376
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:18,240
put her in a tough spot between us.

377
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,000
I even offered her the general manager job

378
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,040
at my factory.

379
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,320
But she wasn't interested.

380
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,160
If she came to work for me,

381
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,240
this chairman would answer to her.

382
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:28,240
Xin Ran and I have worked together so long,

383
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:31,000
always looking out for me, thinking of me.

384
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:33,280
I really don't want to put her in a bind.

385
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,640
Then let's think of another way.

386
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,000
Let me meet with her first

387
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,640
and see what she thinks.

388
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:47,000
Notice anything special about this meal?

389
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:56,120
The first time we came here,

390
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,720
this is exactly what I wore.

391
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,000
The dishes you cooked

392
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:01,400
and even the wine you prepared

393
00:15:01,520 --> 00:15:03,240
are the same brand as that day.

394
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:07,280
So what you're saying is,

395
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,240
where it all began,

396
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,520
that's where it ends.

397
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,200
Never forget why we started,

398
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:16,320
and keep moving forward.

399
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:31,960
Here, try it.

400
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:33,640
The tomato and eggs, I made that.

401
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,000
The rest, I ordered in.

402
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:36,560
No criticism accepted.

403
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:37,640
And no pointers either.

404
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:39,040
My cooking's got no more room to improve.

405
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,080
This is as good as it gets.

406
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:51,200
If I say it's delicious,

407
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:52,720
that's flattery.

408
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,280
Saying it's bad wouldn't be lying either.

409
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:56,320
But unfortunately,

410
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:57,640
your purpose today

411
00:15:57,640 --> 00:15:59,120
isn't just to treat me to dinner.

412
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:01,880
I want us to keep having

413
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,280
happy meals together often.

414
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:05,640
Xuan Yan.

415
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:07,000
The way I see it,

416
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,520
our partnership doesn't have to be affected at all.

417
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:11,520
You really do know me.

418
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:15,360
Go on.

419
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:17,600
What do you want me to do?

420
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:21,120
I know it's hard on you too,

421
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,760
but I still need your help.

422
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,600
Pass this on to Zheng Guohui.

423
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,520
The product patent is mine.

424
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:32,520
I can partner with Dayazhai,

425
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,520
and I also have the right

426
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:37,280
to work with other firms in Taohua Town too.

427
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:41,520
Xuan Yan.

428
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:45,000
What we signed is a binding partnership.

429
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,440
Each side has its own role.

430
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:49,320
You handle only R&D and design,

431
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:51,240
and we represent you

432
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,600
in handling all matters tied to your name.

433
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:54,680
Yes,

434
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,840
the contract doesn't spell it out clearly,

435
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,920
but I still hope you all

436
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,480
can consider my feelings more.

437
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:03,880
Legally speaking,

438
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:05,839
I should be within my rights, right?

439
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:14,440
It can't be that I talk feelings

440
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:16,119
and you talk law with me.

441
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:19,520
Saying that puts me in a tough spot.

442
00:17:24,079 --> 00:17:24,760
Xuan Yan,

443
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:29,600
I think we both value personal loyalty.

444
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,880
Even though we signed a binding deal,

445
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:35,440
I didn't push a legally vetted,

446
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:37,720
hundred-plus-page contract for you to sign.

447
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:42,600
If you really insist on citing the clauses,

448
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:43,920
have you thought about me?

449
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:45,760
Me,

450
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:47,720
Xin Ran, at the company,

451
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,840
what kind of position will I be in?

452
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,520
That's why we're discussing it.

453
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:57,640
It's just the raw pulp material.

454
00:17:58,240 --> 00:18:00,120
These small paper mills in Taohua Town

455
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:02,080
only earn this bit of hard-earned money.

456
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:03,760
For Dayazhai,

457
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:06,280
this is basically nothing, right?

458
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:07,760
But for them,

459
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:09,520
that's their livelihood.

460
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:11,720
It was Dayazhai who proposed it,

461
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:14,120
getting them to switch to making pulp.

462
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,720
Now just walking away, ignoring them,

463
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:21,160
do they even have a conscience?

464
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:23,920
The "they" you're talking about

465
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:26,240
includes me and Dayazhai.

466
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:28,400
Believe it or not,

467
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,440
this decision

468
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:31,240
is hard for me to accept personally.

469
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:33,400
My conscience won't let it rest either.

470
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,400
But I have to accept it.

471
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:36,680
That's reality.

472
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:40,360
Xuan Yan, honestly speaking,

473
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:43,840
I've always envied your freedom and ease.

474
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:47,000
Personally, I find that truly precious.

475
00:18:47,280 --> 00:18:47,960
So,

476
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,480
I'll do everything I can

477
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:53,080
to protect that freedom and ease of yours.

478
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:54,440
But Xuan Yan,

479
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:57,480
I can't do it on my own.

480
00:18:57,760 --> 00:18:59,600
I can only follow the group's orders,

481
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:01,640
only follow the chairman's orders.

482
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,760
Then can I talk to Zheng Guohui directly?

483
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:09,440
Can you swallow your pride?

484
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,600
As long as you can bow down,

485
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:13,400
I'll arrange the meeting.

486
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:19,760
Got it.

487
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:21,960
Forget I ever asked.

488
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:23,400
Come on.

489
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:31,000
Check if there's enough water.

490
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,000
Director Ge.

491
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:34,200
Count how many people we have

492
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,120
attending the meeting today.

493
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:35,720
Alright, alright.

494
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:37,320
You need to hang up this banner, right?

495
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,000
Yes, yes. Hang up the banner.

496
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:41,560
Secretary Peng.

497
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,760
Sorry to take up your time.

498
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,120
I need to report on some work.

499
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:47,560
Thanks for your hard work.

500
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:47,880
It's my duty.

501
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:48,960
Come, come, have a seat.

502
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:50,520
Quick, bring some water.

503
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:52,440
Please, sit down.

504
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:53,960
Thanks for the hard work.

505
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:55,760
Don't mention it.

506
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:56,800
Thank you, thank you.

507
00:19:58,120 --> 00:19:59,160
Let me report to you.

508
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:00,200
Yesterday,

509
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:02,280
I visited those paper mills.

510
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:03,960
For one thing,

511
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,120
to calm everyone's emotions.

512
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:05,840
To ease everyone's feelings.

513
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,160
For another,

514
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:08,440
to get a sense of

515
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:10,440
the difficulties each mill is facing.

516
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,120
Listen to their thoughts,

517
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:15,120
and then discuss solutions.

518
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:16,840
What's the biggest issue now?

519
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:18,360
Workers from several mills

520
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:19,920
feel like they've been deceived.

521
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:21,320
Mentally,

522
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:23,240
they can't come around anytime soon.

523
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:26,520
So, there's no negotiated outcome yet.

524
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:29,160
My suggestion, Secretary Peng,

525
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,520
is that the pulp work

526
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,000
should still go to those small mills.

527
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:34,360
Yiran,

528
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,760
what's your take on this?

529
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:40,160
I hope the businesses in Taohua Town,

530
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:42,360
whether Dayazhai or the small mills,

531
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,880
can unite and develop together.

532
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:47,040
Internal disputes are bad for everyone.

533
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:48,280
What ultimately gets hurt

534
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:50,120
is Taohua Town's Xuan paper industry.

535
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:51,760
Our purpose

536
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:53,480
is to protect everyone's interests.

537
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:55,640
Everyone's interest is our interest.

538
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:57,240
Look at Dayazhai.

539
00:20:57,560 --> 00:20:59,680
They came all the way to Taohua Town.

540
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:00,640
What they'd consider first

541
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,920
is their own interests, right?

542
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:03,760
I think that's perfectly understandable.

543
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:04,920
So I'm worried

544
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:07,440
they won't give face to the other

545
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:09,120
paper mills in Taohua Town.

546
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:13,160
Business is business.

547
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:17,080
Dayazhai has no obligation to do that.

548
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:17,360
Right?

549
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:18,040
Yes, yes, yes.

550
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:18,920
So that's why

551
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:22,720
we need to find an angle on shared interests.

552
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:24,280
Find some common ground with them.

553
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:26,840
Secretary Peng,

554
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:28,040
a while back, Ms. Xin

555
00:21:28,040 --> 00:21:29,240
mentioned something to me.

556
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:30,960
She wants to expand

557
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:32,280
the cultural products sales team.

558
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:33,720
And she wanted to ask us

559
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:35,800
about the newly built e-commerce base.

560
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:37,640
Could we allocate some space for them?

561
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:38,600
I checked into it,

562
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:41,280
and there really is open space we could give them.

563
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,840
If we can offer some price discounts,

564
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:45,040
it works out for both sides.

565
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:46,800
That's no problem.

566
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:48,360
I'll check later

567
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:50,480
with the deputy mayor in charge of this area.

568
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:53,520
As long as it's within policy limits,

569
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:54,600
we'll do our best.

570
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,600
That's wonderful.

571
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:56,280
Yes, yes, yes.

572
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:58,280
I really hope the Association and Dayazhai

573
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:00,320
can jointly form a cooperative.

574
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:01,440
That way,

575
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:04,320
whenever Dayazhai has production needs,

576
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:05,360
they can negotiate with the cooperative.

577
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:06,600
If this deal comes together,

578
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,520
for our Association,

579
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:08,760
it would be a huge help.

580
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:10,560
On behalf of our Association,

581
00:22:10,560 --> 00:22:11,040
What are you doing?

582
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:11,920
I want to thank both of you.

583
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:12,400
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

584
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,680
It's what we should do, right?

585
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:14,320
Come on, have a seat.

586
00:22:14,320 --> 00:22:14,840
Okay, okay, okay.

587
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:15,600
Chairman Xiao,

588
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:18,800
however,

589
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,120
still,

590
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:22,280
I think what you just mentioned

591
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:25,440
may not be feasible under current conditions.

592
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:28,280
So I'll have to work toward that.

593
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:30,600
Remember, too much is as bad as too little.

594
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:33,600
What our government can do right now

595
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:36,120
is only guide and supervise.

596
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,920
We can't handle everything ourselves.

597
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:40,080
Understood.

598
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:41,080
Later on,

599
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,360
get in touch with Ms. Xin.

600
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:46,200
I think Ms. Xin's feelings for Taohua Town

601
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,240
run very deep.

602
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:47,920
Yes, yes, yes.

603
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,040
Even though for many matters,

604
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:51,520
what she says may not be the final word,

605
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:54,360
but as long as she's willing to offer advice,

606
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:57,200
the chances of success will be very high.

607
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,280
Yes, yes, yes.

608
00:22:59,520 --> 00:22:59,960
Alright.

609
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:10,320
Hello.

610
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:17,360
Do you think this needs to be so formal?

611
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:22,520
Alright.

612
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:25,000
Then let's talk in person.

613
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:28,720
The town's come up with a new proposal.

614
00:23:28,720 --> 00:23:30,120
Xuan Yan asked to meet and discuss it.

615
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:31,760
Sister Xin.

616
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:34,360
What on earth is Xuan Yan trying to do?

617
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:35,800
Is he trying to push you into a corner?

618
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:36,760
Let me say a bit more.

619
00:23:36,760 --> 00:23:38,040
Please don't blame me for speaking out.

620
00:23:39,520 --> 00:23:40,200
It's fine.

621
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:41,480
Go ahead.

622
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:42,960
You know,

623
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:44,400
our partnership with Xuan Yan

624
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,880
still has a ticking bomb buried in it.

625
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:47,200
Once it goes off,

626
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:49,840
it could blow us all to pieces.

627
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,920
Don't you feel that how things have unfolded

628
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:55,320
is a bit strange?

629
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:58,360
Xuan Yan clearly has a conflict with the Chairman.

630
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,120
And now Xuan Yan, Lin Yiran, and Xiao Min

631
00:24:00,120 --> 00:24:01,320
have gotten all tangled together,

632
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:02,920
going against Dayazhai.

633
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,680
If this conflict keeps festering,

634
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:08,360
how much patience do you think the Chairman has left?

635
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:11,440
The Chairman's patience isn't just about Xuan Yan.

636
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:12,400
It includes you too.

637
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,200
So you absolutely cannot

638
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:15,440
keep getting tangled up with him.

639
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:17,520
It'll only drain the Chairman's trust in you.

640
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:19,200
It'll drag you down.

641
00:24:23,960 --> 00:24:25,360
Whether from an emotional standpoint,

642
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:26,960
or from a business standpoint,

643
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:30,320
I don't want Xuan Yan to fall out with Dayazhai.

644
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:31,800
He's not just

645
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,520
a great business partner to me,

646
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,120
he's also a very good friend.

647
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:38,920
When it comes to the patent issue,

648
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:41,240
I bear an inescapable responsibility.

649
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:43,320
On that point,

650
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:45,880
I was the one who wronged him first.

651
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:48,920
But you really can't give them any more chances.

652
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,400
You have to make them give up.

653
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:51,600
Otherwise, in the end,

654
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,120
partnership, friendship,

655
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:54,880
you'll lose them all.

656
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:01,360
Sister Xin, take a look.

657
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:04,200
I've mainly considered three points.

658
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:05,440
First,

659
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:07,400
running your own mill to produce pulp,

660
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:08,840
no matter how you calculate the cost,

661
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:10,800
it'll actually be much higher

662
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:11,600
than Taohua Town's cost.

663
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:12,360
Chairman Xiao,

664
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:14,240
you could negotiate with the mills again,

665
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:15,640
see if the price can

666
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:17,520
come down by about ten percent more.

667
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:19,080
That way, we can cut costs

668
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:20,600
for Dayazhai to the greatest extent.

669
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:21,960
Second,

670
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:24,360
Secretary Peng has agreed

671
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:26,200
to allocate a space for Dayazhai

672
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:27,640
in the newly built e-commerce base.

673
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:30,360
This ensures Dayazhai can expand

674
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:32,080
and develop to the greatest extent.

675
00:25:33,360 --> 00:25:34,360
From a development standpoint,

676
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:35,960
I think the third point is the most important.

677
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:36,840
And that is,

678
00:25:37,040 --> 00:25:39,160
in this newly formed e-commerce alliance system,

679
00:25:39,160 --> 00:25:40,840
we'll bring Dayazhai in.

680
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:41,920
This means

681
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,520
the talent across the entire alliance

682
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:45,040
is all available for Dayazhai to work with.

683
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:47,680
Whether in marketing, promotion, or sales,

684
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,320
we can use different approaches

685
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:51,040
to give Dayazhai a boost.

686
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:51,840
This way,

687
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:53,160
Dayazhai can substantially

688
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,680
reduce its costs,

689
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:57,160
while also achieving the best results.

690
00:25:57,320 --> 00:25:58,120
What do you think?

691
00:25:58,920 --> 00:25:59,920
I think it sounds great.

692
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:00,560
Right?

693
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:06,040
Why do I feel like

694
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:09,080
the Six Sects are laying siege to Bright Peak?

695
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:19,880
I'm not on anyone's side.

696
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:20,920
I'm on your side.

697
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:23,200
No, Sister Xin,

698
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:25,120
setting aside our roles,

699
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:26,840
we're still friends, aren't we?

700
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:28,960
We all want to solve this together.

701
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:30,360
We don't want to put you in a tough spot.

702
00:26:30,520 --> 00:26:31,360
We're not thinking anything else.

703
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:32,360
We just want to help you.

704
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:34,400
Xin Ran,

705
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:36,040
if...

706
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:38,200
you still trust us,

707
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:39,280
if we're still family,

708
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:41,320
then tell us what's troubling you.

709
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:42,800
That way we won't have to guess.

710
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:43,600
If we guess wrong,

711
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:44,680
we might just make things worse.

712
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:45,560
That wouldn't be good, would it?

713
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:46,840
Yeah, Sister Xin.

714
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:48,080
Just tell us what the problem is.

715
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:49,160
We'll solve it together.

716
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:51,920
Fine.

717
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:53,400
We're friends,

718
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:55,280
so I'll be straight with you.

719
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,120
The best thing you can do for me

720
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:58,960
is, starting right now,

721
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:00,920
don't take any more action.

722
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:02,080
Dayazhai doesn't need

723
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:03,920
any cooperation with Taohua Town.

724
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:06,120
If I've caused you two any trouble,

725
00:27:06,120 --> 00:27:08,120
I hope you can help clean things up.

726
00:27:08,120 --> 00:27:09,800
I don't want this matter

727
00:27:09,800 --> 00:27:12,440
to be endlessly debated and dragged out.

728
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:13,720
Whatever the outcome,

729
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:15,520
all I can offer is my sincerest apology.

730
00:27:15,520 --> 00:27:17,080
I have nothing else to say.

731
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:17,600
That's it.

732
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:18,280
Ms. Xin.

733
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:18,920
Ms. Xin. Ms. Xin.

734
00:27:18,920 --> 00:27:20,360
Wait, Sister Xin,

735
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:22,040
can't the town step in directly

736
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:23,520
and talk to your chairman instead?

737
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:24,840
You wouldn't need to be involved.

738
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:26,880
My position is crystal clear.

739
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:28,160
No need to repeat it.

740
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:30,560
I understand you're under huge pressure at work.

741
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:31,800
And I get that

742
00:27:31,800 --> 00:27:32,760
whether Taohua Town's businesses thrive

743
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:33,440
has nothing to do with you.

744
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:34,600
But what I don't get is,

745
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:37,040
why can't you stand up for justice?

746
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:38,840
Why can't Xuan Yan, as a partner,

747
00:27:38,840 --> 00:27:40,040
exercise his rights?

748
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:41,600
And also, why

749
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:43,960
no matter what absurd reason the chairman gives,

750
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:45,120
do you have to back him unconditionally?

751
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:46,040
Why?

752
00:27:47,080 --> 00:27:47,880
Lin Yiran,

753
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:50,320
I thought you understood me.

754
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:52,280
Turns out you don't understand a thing.

755
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:54,360
Ms. Xin. Ms. Xin.

756
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:55,560
No, I don't understand.

757
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:56,560
Stop, stop, stop.

758
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:57,720
Xuan Yan. Xuan Yan. Xuan Yan.

759
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:58,480
I'll go talk to her.

760
00:27:58,960 --> 00:27:59,800
Ms. Xin.

761
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:06,040
Yiran.

762
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:16,680
Enough.

763
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:24,040
I feel like Xin Ran has something she can't say.

764
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:24,800
She doesn't know

765
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:26,560
how to tell us.

766
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:29,320
I don't see why I can't go see Zheng Guohui.

767
00:28:29,360 --> 00:28:31,280
I don't see how that would hurt Sister Xin.

768
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:33,600
So why is she so desperate to stop me?

769
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:35,520
So many people need our help,

770
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:37,160
we could help but we're not.

771
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:38,200
Why?

772
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:42,120
I totally understand how you feel.

773
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:43,720
I'm torn too.

774
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:45,840
But then again,

775
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:48,680
none of us

776
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:50,520
has the right to demand anything from her,

777
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:52,800
even if we think it's the right thing.

778
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:54,360
How about this?

779
00:28:55,040 --> 00:28:57,920
Let's give each other some space.

780
00:28:58,400 --> 00:28:59,200
Right?

781
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:00,800
Time might smooth all of this out.

782
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:01,880
No, what do you mean?

783
00:29:03,120 --> 00:29:04,040
Me? I... I...

784
00:29:04,040 --> 00:29:05,080
I really can't follow what you're saying.

785
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:06,040
I'm just saying,

786
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:07,680
give yourself some time.

787
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:10,280
Your... bag.

788
00:29:14,800 --> 00:29:16,720
That's why I say I can always count on you, Min.

789
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:18,120
Having instant noodles with me.

790
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:20,360
I'm starving.

791
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:21,600
I sat there all afternoon.

792
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:22,920
Coaxing and persuading her,

793
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:24,120
but Xin Ran wouldn't listen.

794
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,400
The way those two were today,

795
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:27,920
that whole situation,

796
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:29,120
if Xin Ran hadn't left,

797
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:30,840
there'd have been no way to end it.

798
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:33,160
The old saying is right,

799
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:34,720
three women make a whole drama.

800
00:29:34,720 --> 00:29:36,840
Even two women are more than we can handle.

801
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:40,800
Lin Yiran,

802
00:29:41,560 --> 00:29:43,360
how's she doing? Any better?

803
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:45,000
Take a guess.

804
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:47,720
Let me guess.

805
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:48,920
With her temper,

806
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:50,600
after being wronged like that, she's fuming.

807
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:53,200
But honestly speaking,

808
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:54,600
I really do admire

809
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:56,160
the way she stands her ground.

810
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:58,120
Including her business sense,

811
00:29:58,280 --> 00:29:59,640
I really do appreciate that too.

812
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:01,920
As for Lin Yiran,

813
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:04,800
she wants to talk to Zheng Guohui directly.

814
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:08,720
I told her to slow down,

815
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:10,360
cool off first,

816
00:30:10,560 --> 00:30:11,520
and not rush into it.

817
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:14,640
Talk to Zheng Guohui about what?

818
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:18,040
To defend your bottom line with Dayazhai.

819
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:21,960
What if Zheng Guohui keeps this attitude?

820
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:23,040
Xuan Yan,

821
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:27,040
your contract with Dayazhai is non-exclusive.

822
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:30,760
You just need to grant them

823
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:31,920
the patent usage rights.

824
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:33,040
That way,

825
00:30:33,880 --> 00:30:35,840
you could work with our association too, right?

826
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:37,240
We'd form a cooperative

827
00:30:37,800 --> 00:30:38,960
and make your creative products.

828
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:40,600
Running the offline market, isn't that great?

829
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:42,920
That's your own idea, isn't it?

830
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:46,960
Who wouldn't want to make money?

831
00:30:47,120 --> 00:30:48,120
Besides, even if I'm not eyeing it,

832
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:49,280
plenty of others are.

833
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,040
Like who?

834
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:51,960
The Xuan paper factory bosses,

835
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:53,400
including those in our association.

836
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:54,960
They're actually quite interested

837
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:56,440
in forming this cooperative.

838
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:57,440
They all want to join in.

839
00:30:57,560 --> 00:30:58,320
I said, hold on, hold on.

840
00:30:58,320 --> 00:31:00,160
I said, let me talk to Xuan Yan first.

841
00:31:01,680 --> 00:31:02,760
Even though

842
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:05,920
what I signed with Dayazhai

843
00:31:05,920 --> 00:31:08,120
is a non-exclusive cooperation deal,

844
00:31:09,120 --> 00:31:10,800
in Xin Ran's mind,

845
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:12,120
the two of us are tied together.

846
00:31:12,560 --> 00:31:13,560
If we

847
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,920
